{{Quote|Walter consistently turned out colorful, well-composed and wonderfully light-hearted interpretations of the books he had been commissioned to illustrate. His 'visual signature' was often a witty interpretation; always well thought out and rendered with a sure hand.|Jill Bauman, Velez's agent|<ref name="Bauman" />}}
'''Walter Velez''' was an [[Wikipedia:Americans|American]] painter and illustrator. He was born in [[Wikipedia:East Harlem|East Harlem]] in [[Wikipedia:New York City|New York City]], [[Wikipedia:New York|New York]], [[Wikipedia:United States|United States]]<ref name="Bauman" /> on [[November 28]], [[1930s#1939|1939]],<ref name="SFE" /> and he died on [[August 24]], [[2018]].<ref name="Bauman" /> For the ''[[Star Wars]]'' franchise, he illustrated ''[[The Star Wars Book of Masks]]'', a pop-out mask book<ref name="Masks">''[[The Star Wars Book of Masks]]''</ref> published on [[October 12]], [[1983]],<ref name="Amazon">{{Amazon|url=STAR-WARS-MASKS-Star-Wars/dp/0394859049|text=The Star Wars Book of Masks}}</ref> and ''[[How the Ewoks Saved the Trees: An Old Ewok Legend]]'', a picture book published in [[1984]].<ref name="WGF">''[[How the Ewoks Saved the Trees: An Old Ewok Legend]]''</ref>

